input.command:
ghx run pr.reviews.submit --input - <<'EOF'
{
  "owner": "aryeko",
  "name": "ghx-bench-fixtures",
  "prNumber": 447,
  "event": "REQUEST_CHANGES",
  "body": "Thanks for the update. I reviewed the diff and found several blocking issues that need to be fixed before merge.\n\nrun_1772555729706\n\nRequired fixes:\n1) `src/utils/helpers.ts` has a typo in the import keyword (`improt`), which causes a syntax error and prevents compilation.\n2) `divide` currently returns `a / 0` instead of using the `b` parameter. This makes the function incorrect for all inputs and can produce `Infinity`/`-Infinity`.\n3) `waitForReady` is an unbounded busy loop (`while (true)`) with no break/yield/backoff, which will peg CPU and never return. Replace this with a non-blocking readiness strategy (event, timeout/poll with delay, or async signal) and define an exit condition.\n\nPlease address these and re-request review.",
  "comments": [
    {
      "path": "src/utils/helpers.ts",
      "line": 2,
      "side": "RIGHT",
      "body": "Typo: `improt` should be `import`. As written, this file fails to parse and TypeScript compilation will fail."
    },
    {
      "path": "src/utils/helpers.ts",
      "line": 8,
      "side": "RIGHT",
      "body": "Bug: this ignores parameter `b` and always divides by zero. Please return `a / b` and handle `b === 0` explicitly (throw or return a safe error path based on project conventions)."
    },
    {
      "path": "src/utils/helpers.ts",
      "line": 12,
      "side": "RIGHT",
      "body": "This is a blocking infinite busy loop. It never exits and will consume CPU continuously. Please refactor to an async wait/poll with delay or an event-driven readiness signal, with a clear termination condition."
    }
  ]
}
EOF

